The paper deals with a communication strategy for DC Micro Grids, which involves modulating power levels in the DC bus. This involves the use of power electronics and control systems, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.PE (Power and Energy), cs.ET (Embedded Systems), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering). Among these, cs.SY and cs.IT are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with communication and control systems, while cs.PE, cs.ET, and cs.CE are also relevant due to the use of power electronics and embedded systems.
